.TH "verify_pkcs7_signature" 9 "verify_pkcs7_signature" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
verify_pkcs7_signature \- Verify a PKCS#7-based signature on system data.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" verify_pkcs7_signature
.BI "(const void *data "  ","
.BI "size_t len "  ","
.BI "const void *raw_pkcs7 "  ","
.BI "size_t pkcs7_len "  ","
.BI "struct key *trusted_keys "  ","
.BI "enum key_being_used_for usage "  ","
.BI "int (*view_content)(void *ctx, const void *data, size_t len, size_t asn1hdrlen) "  ","
.BI "void *ctx "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "data" 12
The data to be verified (NULL if expecting internal data).
.IP "len" 12
Size of \fIdata\fP.
.IP "raw_pkcs7" 12
The PKCS#7 message that is the signature.
.IP "pkcs7_len" 12
The size of \fIraw_pkcs7\fP.
.IP "trusted_keys" 12
Trusted keys to use (NULL for builtin trusted keys only,
(void *)1UL for all trusted keys).
.IP "usage" 12
The use to which the key is being put.
.IP "view_content" 12
Callback to gain access to content.
.IP "ctx" 12
Context for callback.
